Name: BMW
Description: BMW cars are renowned for their exceptional performance, handling, and engineering, making them the perfect choice for those who crave a thrilling driving experience. With innovative technology such as iDrive, advanced safety features, and luxurious interiors, a BMW is not just a car - it's a lifestyle. Upgrade your driving game and experience the ultimate in luxury with a BMW

Name: Audi
Description: The AUDI AG stands for sporty vehicles, high build quality and progressive design – for “Vorsprung durch Technik.” The Audi Group is among the world's leading producers of premium cars

Name: Brezza
Description: Brezza has its basics in place. A smooth petrol engine, a spacious cabin, and a very comfortable ride quality. Compared to the diesel, you’d appreciate not just the refinement of the motor, but also the smooth nature of the automatic compared to the AMT.

Name: Fortuner
Description: Toyota Fortuner is a 7 seater SUV with a mileage of 10 Kmpl depending upon it's transmission and fuel type. Fortuner's 4 cylinder, 2755 cc, 2.8 L Diesel engine can generate 165 PS @ 5200 rpm power and 245 Nm @ 4000 rpm torque. It has a fuel tank capacity of 80 Litres L.

Name: Tata Nano
Description: One of the most iconic small cars in the Indian market, the Tata Nano has lived a hard life so far, however, it doesn’t take away the fact that it’s an extremely practical city car with a spacious cabin. The Nano is also efficient and easy to drive thanks to the tiny turning radius and light controls.

Name: Hyundai i10
Description: The Hyundai i10 has 2 Petrol Engine and 1 LPG Engine on offer. The Petrol engine is 1086 cc and 1197 cc while the LPG engine is 1086 cc . It is available with Manual & Automatic transmission.Depending upon the variant and fuel type the i10 has a mileage of 16.95 to 20.36 kmpl & Ground clearance of i10 is 165mm. The i10 is a 5 seater 4 cylinder car and has length of 3585mm, width of 1595mm and a wheelbase of 2380mm.
